Neta-Resume — data source attributions & usage notice
======================================================

This is a NON-COMMERCIAL / hobby project. It aggregates and re-presents data from
public sources about elected representatives in India. Attribution and usage terms
for each upstream source:

1. MyNeta / Association for Democratic Reforms (ADR) / National Election Watch
   https://www.myneta.info/  ·  https://adrindia.org/
   - Data derived from ECI self-sworn candidate affidavits (assets, liabilities,
     income, criminal cases, education).
   - Licensed for NON-COMMERCIAL use only. No bulk CSV is provided; data is
     scraped politely from per-candidate pages with caching and rate limiting.
   - ADR transcribes affidavits (OCR + manual entry); MyNeta is NOT a byte-for-byte
     mirror of ECI. Treat ECI affidavit PDFs as the canonical legal source.

2. Election Commission of India (ECI)
   https://affidavit.eci.gov.in/  ·  https://www.eci.gov.in/
   - Canonical affidavit PDFs. Used for verification.

3. Digital Sansad (Lok Sabha & Rajya Sabha Secretariats)
   https://sansad.in/
   - Official member roster and profiles.

4. Trivedi Centre for Political Data (TCPD), Ashoka University
   - SURF entity-resolution system; LokDhaba / Political Career Tracker datasets.
   https://tcpd.ashoka.edu.in/  ·  https://lokdhaba.ashoka.edu.in/
   - Academic use; cite TCPD-IPD where their IDs/data are used.

5. eCourts / bharat-courts / openjustice-in
   https://services.ecourts.gov.in/  ·  https://github.com/iamshouvikmitra/bharat-courts
   - Court case status enrichment.

6. data.gov.in (Open Government Data Platform India)
   https://www.data.gov.in/  ·  Government Open Data License – India (GODL).

7. DataMeet / Vonter parsed affidavit corpora (community), OpenSanctions in_sansad.

USAGE PRINCIPLES
- Every datapoint shown carries a link to its source.
- Criminal cases are mostly PENDING/ALLEGED. The site always shows pending-vs-convicted
  status and never asserts guilt. See docs/data-license.md and docs/severity-rubric.md.
- This project does not represent the views of any source above.
